t 9. ln the mancipatory form of will no witness might be in the potestas of either the testator or familiae emptor, Gaius ii. 105. The incapacity of a paterfamilias or any one in his power to witness his own son's will of castrense peculium, though affirmed by Justinian here after Gaius (ii. 106), is denied by Ulpian in bigat. 1. 20. 2 on the authority of Marcellus. Probably the two passages relate to different cases ε the latter to a will made by the son as soldier, that before us to one made after discharge.
